# Security Rules

References:

- docs/tech-architecture.md
- docs/coding-standards.md
- docs/deployment-guide.md

---

# Purpose

Protect:

- User Accounts
- Financial Data
- Affiliate Data
- Withdrawal Operations
- Administrative Functions

Security takes precedence over convenience.

---

# Security Principles

Follow:

Least Privilege

Defense In Depth

Zero Trust

Secure By Default

---

# Authentication Rules

Provider

Google OAuth

JWT

Refresh Token

---

Passwords are not supported in MVP.

---

Never trust:

- Frontend state
- Request body role
- Query parameters

---

Authentication source:

Validated JWT only.

---

# Authorization Rules

All endpoints require authorization unless explicitly public.

---

Public Endpoints

Health Check

Google Login

OAuth Callback

Webhook Endpoint

---

Everything else:

Authenticated.

---

# Role Based Access

Roles:

User

Admin

---

User

Can access:

Own Data Only

---

Admin

Can access:

Administrative Features

---

Never expose admin features to normal users.

---

# Ownership Validation

Critical Requirement

Users may only access their own:

- Orders
- Withdrawals
- Notifications
- Affiliate Links

---

Always verify:

CurrentUserId == ResourceOwnerId

---

Never trust:

UserId from frontend.

---

# JWT Rules

Required Claims

UserId

Email

Role

---

Access Token Lifetime

Recommended

15 Minutes

---

Refresh Token Lifetime

Recommended

30 Days

---

Values must be configurable.

---

# Refresh Token Rules

Store in database.

Suggested Fields

- Token
- UserId
- ExpiresAt
- RevokedAt

---

Never store plaintext tokens.

Store hashes only.

---

# Secret Management

Secrets must not exist in source code.

---

Forbidden

```csharp
var secret = "my-secret";
```

---

Use:

Environment Variables

Secret Manager

Configuration Provider

---

Examples

JWT Secret

Database Connection String

Google Client Secret

Webhook Secret

Provider Tokens

---

# Password Rules

MVP

No passwords.

---

Future

Use:

BCrypt

Argon2

---

Never use:

MD5

SHA1

Custom Hashing

---

# API Security

Enable HTTPS only.

---

Reject:

HTTP requests in production.

---

Use:

HSTS

Secure Headers

---

# CORS Rules

Whitelist origins.

---

Bad

```csharp
AllowAnyOrigin()
```

---

Production

Explicit Origins Only.

---

# Input Validation

All inputs must be validated.

Use:

FluentValidation

---

Never trust:

Request payloads.

---

Validation required for:

URLs

Amounts

Identifiers

Filters

Pagination

---

# SQL Injection Protection

Use:

Entity Framework Core

Parameterized Queries

---

Never concatenate SQL strings.

---

Forbidden

```csharp
"SELECT - FROM Users WHERE Id=" + userId
```

---

# XSS Protection

Frontend must:

Escape user content.

---

Never render raw HTML unless explicitly required.

---

Use React default escaping.

---

# CSRF Rules

JWT API

Low Risk

---

Future

Enable anti-forgery for cookie-based auth.

---

# Rate Limiting

Required

Examples

Login

10 requests / minute

---

Affiliate Link Generation

100 requests / hour

---

Webhook Endpoint

Provider-specific limits

---

Values configurable.

---

# Financial Security

Critical Requirement

Balance changes only occur through:

Orders Module

Withdrawals Module

---

Admin cannot directly modify balances.

---

Every financial action must create audit records.

---

# Withdrawal Security

Validate:

Ownership

Available Balance

Status Transition

---

All withdrawal actions must be logged.

---

# Webhook Security

Required

Signature Validation

Secret Validation

Replay Protection

---

Never process unverified webhooks.

---

# File Upload Rules

Future Feature

Validate:

File Type

File Size

File Extension

---

Never trust MIME type alone.

---

# Logging Rules

Never log:

Passwords

Tokens

Secrets

Refresh Tokens

Connection Strings

Bank Account Numbers

---

Sensitive data must be masked.

---

# Audit Requirements

Must Audit

Withdrawal Approval

Withdrawal Rejection

Settings Changes

User Suspension

Admin Actions

---

Audit logs must be immutable.

---

# Dependency Security

Update dependencies regularly.

---

Do not use:

Abandoned Packages

Unknown Packages

---

Prefer:

Official Libraries

Well Maintained Libraries

---

# Security Headers

Recommended

Content-Security-Policy

X-Content-Type-Options

X-Frame-Options

Referrer-Policy

---

# Testing Requirements

✓ Authorization

✓ Authentication

✓ Ownership Validation

✓ Token Expiration

✓ Refresh Token Rotation

✓ Rate Limiting

✓ Input Validation

✓ Webhook Validation

✓ Security Headers

---

